---
import fs from 'node:fs';
import path from 'node:path';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { IEEE_DATAPORT_HASHTAG_SEARCH } from '../lib/linkedin';

const bookmarkletPath = path.join(process.cwd(), 'public/tools/bookmarklet.href');
const bookmarkletHref = fs.existsSync(bookmarkletPath)
  ? fs.readFileSync(bookmarkletPath, 'utf8').trim()
  : '';
---

<Layout
  title="Editor tools · IEEE DataPort Member Voices"
  description="Bookmarklet and intake tools for editorial #ieeedataport curation."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Editor tools</h1>
    <p>
      Human-in-the-loop helpers for curating public <strong>#ieeedataport</strong> posts.
      These tools do not scrape LinkedIn automatically — you browse and capture with consent.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>1. LinkedIn capture bookmarklet</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      While logged into LinkedIn, open a post from
      <a href={IEEE_DATAPORT_HASHTAG_SEARCH} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        #ieeedataport search
      </a>,
      then click the bookmarklet. A <code>linkedin-staging.csv</code> row is copied to your clipboard.
    </p>

    {bookmarkletHref ? (
      <div class="bookmarklet-box">
        <a class="bookmarklet-btn" href={bookmarkletHref}>
          IEEE DP Capture
        </a>
        <p class="muted small">
          Drag this button to your bookmarks bar (Chrome: show bookmarks bar → drag link).
        </p>
      </div>
    ) : (
      <p class="muted">
        Bookmarklet not built yet. Run <code>python3 scripts/build_bookmarklet.py</code> before <code>npm run build</code>.
      </p>
    )}

    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Install the bookmarklet (drag link above).</li>
      <li>Open a LinkedIn post that mentions IEEE DataPort or <code>#ieeedataport</code>.</li>
      <li>Click <strong>IEEE DP Capture</strong> — CSV row copies to clipboard.</li>
      <li>Paste into <code>data/linkedin-staging.csv</code> in the repo.</li>
      <li>Commit and push, or wait for the daily pipeline after merge.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>2. Member form import</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Members can submit via the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}submit/`}>Submit page</a>,
      a <a href="https://github.com/SJTU-YONGFU-RESEARCH-GRP/ieee-dp-sharing/issues/new?template=member-submission.yml">GitHub issue</a>,
      or a Google Form. Download the form CSV and import:
    </p>
    <pre class="code-block">python3 scripts/import_form_export.py data/inbox/member-form-export.csv
python3 scripts/merge_staging.py</pre>
    <p class="muted">
      See <code>docs/MEMBER_SUBMISSION.md</code> for Google Form field names and setup.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>3. Automated imports</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/import_ieee_stories.py</code> — all case studies in <code>data/ieee-story-sources.json</code></li>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/twitter_import.py</code> — <code>@IEEEDataPort</code> (needs <code>TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN</code>)</li>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/facebook_import.py</code> — IEEE DataPort Page (needs <code>FACEBOOK_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN</code>)</li>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/linkedin_import.py</code> — IEEE org page (needs LinkedIn API)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>4. Pipeline commands</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/merge_staging.py</code> — CSV → entries.json</li>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/score_entries.py --apply</code> — content filter</li>
      <li><code>python3 scripts/enrich.py</code> — sentiment/topics</li>
      <li><code>./scripts/daily-pipeline.sh</code> — full refresh + deploy trigger</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .bookmarklet-box {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .bookmarklet-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white !important;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .small {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0;
  }

  .steps {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .code-block {
    background: #0f1722;
    color: #e8eef7;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
</style>
